                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The President of the General Assembly put the draft resolution on Jerusalem
                    contained in the report of the <hi rend="italic">Ad Hoc</hi> Political Committee
                    to a vote on December 15. There was no discussion of the measure. The result was
                    thirty votes in favor, eighteen opposed, and nine abstentions. The United States
                    and the United Kingdom were recorded in opposition; the Soviet Union abstained.
                    Inasmuch as the measure failed to obtain the required two-thirds majority, the
                    draft resolution failed of adoption (<gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> (V), <hi
                        rend="italic">Plenary</hi>, page 684).</p>
            </div>
        </body>
